      <hedline>
        <hl1>In Our S.U.V.'s: A Love-Hate Story</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Joel Felstiner letter on Feb 8 article deplores SUVs; drawing</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It is disheartening to hear S.U.V. owners like the Marin County mother: ''How else am I going to get four children from A to B?'' (news article, Feb. 8). Our Toyota Corolla seated four kids easily, my own two plus their friends.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It is disheartening to hear S.U.V. owners like the Marin County mother: ''How else am I going to get four children from A to B?'' (news article, Feb. 8). Our Toyota Corolla seated four kids easily, my own two plus their friends.</p>
        <p>How shortsighted and arrogant for Americans to think that our super-consumption does not directly, immediately, jeopardize us and the rest of the world through global warming, oil dependency and the plundering of ever scantier resources!</p>
        <p>JOHN FELSTINER  Stanford, Calif., Feb. 8, 2003</p>
      </block>
